nrelated, but still, should I leave it as is? I’m also thinking about the `git diff` command; it doesn’t show untracked files, so maybe I don’t need to modify it. Also, would there be a compile issue with package-private access? I’m not sure.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Deciding on Class Accessibility**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering whether to make a method private to limit exposure. It seems like calling a private nested method from an outer class is fine, and maybe using `private final` is better. I wonder if I could define the nested class as `public static final`—that would be interesting, but reflection is still a factor. Adding a `serialVersionUID` isn't required, but since the nested class is serializable, I have to keep potential warnings in mind. If a Native Image compile occurs from generated metadata, it should be included, right?\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Clarifying test instructions**\\\\n\\\\nI need to clarify that the tests weren't run as per the developer's explicit instructions. I'm thinking I should say they aren't run. If I'm adding a new file, the Git status might still show untracked metadata. I want to avoid a lengthy note like \\\\\\\"pre-existing untracked metadata directory remains untouched,\\\\\\\" but I should keep it concise. It could be wise to mention, \\\\\\\"I did not modify the metadata.\\\\\\\"\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Implemented focused coverage for `CollectionPathBase`.\\n\\nChanges:\\n- Added `tests/src/com.querydsl/querydsl-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/com_querydsl/querydsl_core/CollectionPathBaseTest.java`\\n  - Exercises all four constructor-selection branches in `CollectionPathBase.newInstance`:\\n    - typed query type with `PathInits` constructor (`BeanPath`)\\n    - typed query type without `PathInits` constructor (`SimplePath`)\\n    - non-typed query type with `PathInits` constructor (`NonTypedPathWithInits`)\\n    - non-typed query type without 