t doesn’t show untracked files, so maybe I don’t need to modify it. Also, would there be a compile issue with package-private access? I’m not sure.\\n\\n**Deciding on Class Accessibility**\\n\\nI’m considering whether to make a method private to limit exposure. It seems like calling a private nested method from an outer class is fine, and maybe using `private final` is better. I wonder if I could define the nested class as `public static final`—that would be interesting, but reflection is still a factor. Adding a `serialVersionUID` isn't required, but since the nested class is serializable, I have to keep potential warnings in mind. If a Native Image compile occurs from generated metadata, it should be included, right?\\n\\n**Clarifying test instructions**\\n\\nI need to clarify that the tests weren't run as per the developer's explicit instructions. I'm thinking I should say they aren't run. If I'm adding a new file, the Git status might still show untracked metadata. I want to avoid a lengthy note like \\\"pre-existing untracked metadata directory remains untouched,\\\" but I should keep it concise. It could be wise to mention, \\\"I did not modify the metadata.\\\"\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0a75812b0c7affc00169f9298098e8819491188020cdcc6173\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-SmNoBxXbqlBJ5vHalM-dZ3h8bYLl6ZwiIi49N6-xpqHXoxJVX-BziZxkcsVtCyewesJSlLAORPhsuW1Snxd6BOHuTa_AcIY4bOby2xYBI4nUpZjZKsItI57mQJHOUlsFVQSlEDr83KLsKJdpLmne-FGy1o_MjjKiyGCBX3ZbeLxfLYyb_83AyEsFgTO5xmD0Ye0IoG_n-8SLYeR8JHT0-_YoSesQa-gIWTv73SwzT7dPmNyWy_i-_yvkLkZgcQ3ZoQqGs7NUuM8yaTiCeMXDtupaw5UR8Z5t6oGGOcErOaaom1fuVoMnPg4r1tGUjwhVdTUwztbvZeusLZ3I8L3wSZ7buiqnmEUwYz1Tf4-dIZkMpmua5rqtMnMVwWVU07e7nt0rQyfl-8gi4FFSNDC13RtKMOx_lyazSppFN8N2xXXjr7iVwZHjMzLCdl6Dkh7vRieybP5O7qJu4HU0mvFiXkE7BMOKTLS6tOKZqRlNyiKl4o2AYAXk05gyDq9Z9zmr5Fpyq8ApAvYVXkoUASvD4ZFEcY7wyYlaUAaJjpEC-bi7jMmqYI5QibpvYEG4FcB1uEmeScAqFMuLCfvajoQeOaejR4juSgmzAwk6BD4D3YQtbghWm8QcmY7WiO43WbXwL